Nvidia has opened pre-orders for its Quadro RTX 6000 graphics card, aimed at professional users. Tom’s Hardware reported that the card will sell for $6,300 – and stock is limited to five per customer. The Quadro RTX 6000 is aimed at users in the film, automotive, architectural, and scientific industries. It packs 4,608 CUDA cores, 576 Tensor cores, and 72 RT cores for ray tracing. It also features 24GB of GDDR6 memory across a 384-bit interface. This allows the graphics card to produce 16.3 TFLOPS of single precision performance. “It is also capable of delivering up to 10 GigaRays/sec of ray tracing performance, 84 Tera RTX-OPS, and 130.5 Tensor TFLOPS,” said Tom’s Hardware.